title: SRC-.4: SRC-0003: Requirements
subtitle: This section includes the documents of the CHILD system.  It is divided into two main sections: functional requirements and non-functional requirements.

children.title: SRC-.4.1: SRC-0002: About this document
children.subtitle: The CHILD system has to fulfill the requirements in this document.

children.title: SRC-.4.2: SRC-0004: Functional requirements
children.subtitle: This section defines the functional requirements of the CHILD system.  These functional requirements are the main reason why the CHILD system has to be developed.

children.title: SRC-.4.2.1: SRC-0005: Speed
children.subtitle: The system shall operate at an SysSpeed greater than 30 +/- 0.01 fps

children.title: SRC-.4.2.2: SRC-0006: Contrast
children.subtitle: The system shall provide images which ImgContrast is greater than 20 +/-  1 %

children.title: SRC-.4.2.3: SRC-0007: Detector sensitivity
children.subtitle: The detector shall provide a DtcSensitivity greater than 3000 +/- 2 wtf

children.title: SRC-.4.2.4: SRC-0008: Detector controller
children.subtitle: The detector controller shall be able to operate at DtcCtrlSpeed greater than 32 +/- 0.01 fps

children.title: SRC-.4.3: SRC-0009: Non-functional requirements
children.subtitle: This section defines the non-functional requirements of the CHILD system.  They set the quality level of the system to be developed.

children.title: SRC-.4.3.1: SRC-0010: Availability
children.subtitle: The system shall be available an SysAvailability value greater than 95 +/- 0.1 %
